      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/40/794",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ مُوسَى بْنَ جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِمَا اَلسَّلاَمُ يَقُولُ: «مَا أَكَلَ اَلْوَرَقَ وَ اَلشَّجَرَ فَلاَ بَأْسَ بِأَنْ تُصَلِّيَ فِيهِ وَ مَا أَكَلَ اَلْمَيْتَةَ فَلاَ تُصَلِّ فِيهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.794 - It was narrated from Hashim Al Hannat that he heard Imam Musa ibn Jafar Al-Kadhim (as) say:\n\"Anything that eats leaves and plants, there is no problem in praying while wearing it (its leather or fur), but anything that eats carrion, do not pray in it”."
        ]
      }
    },
